While the church and some women would rather live in an unhappy marriage, the continued mockery they receive when they stay in unhappy marriages contradicts the countrys policies, specifically the constitution of Tonga (801). Most women dont speak up in marriage because they see divorce as punishment, and fear that their families would suffer or that it could lead to a worse future for the children.
